OL,7,FPhysically uncompromising, he was
OL,8,Falready no stranger to concussion and
OL,9,Fits effects on the body.
OL,11,F"There was a particular incident when
OL,12,Fhe had a trial", remembers Andrew. "He
OL,13,Fwas knocked unconscious clearly.
OL,15,F"When he came around he was left in
OL,16,Fthe dressing room on his own. He had
OL,17,Fno idea where he was, didn't know
OL,18,Fwhere the showers were, he had no one
OL,19,Faround him.
