OL,3,C'Every hit has an impact': the
OL,4,Cirreversible toll of concussions on
OL,5,Crugby players
OL,7,F"He was absolutely dumfounded that
OL,8,Fhe'd connected his hot water to his
OL,9,Fgas. He just couldn't get his head
OL,10,Faround it.
OL,12,F"And he became increasingly agitated
OL,13,Fand stressed about not being able to
OL,14,Fcarry out and completely routine
OL,15,Fworks, to the point that he decided he
OL,16,Fhad to leave his job."
OL,18,F"He sadly became a bit of recluse. He
OL,19,Fstopped going out, he became very
OL,20,Fquiet."
